152
00:09:42,083 --> 00:09:44,500
I wouldn't go that far,
but it is a possibility.

153
00:09:48,708 --> 00:09:50,875
I know that was
no ordinary dream.

154
00:09:50,958 --> 00:09:52,458
It seemed so real.

155
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:06,208
Naru?

156
00:10:06,291 --> 00:10:09,333
Now this is a dream
I've had before.

157
00:10:09,416 --> 00:10:10,375
So Naru...

158
00:10:10,458 --> 00:10:11,666
Ayami...

159
00:10:11,750 --> 00:10:12,916
Do you really think
we can save her

160
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:15,416
before it's too late?

161
00:10:15,500 --> 00:10:17,291
She'll be fine.

162
00:10:17,375 --> 00:10:18,625
Really?

163
00:10:20,583 --> 00:10:21,875
You're right.

164
00:10:21,958 --> 00:10:24,375
As long as we do our best,
everything will work out.

165
00:10:24,458 --> 00:10:26,458
Are you sure that's
a good idea, Naru?

166
00:10:32,625 --> 00:10:34,083
He's back!

167
00:10:34,166 --> 00:10:36,625
Lin. Play back everything
you've recorded thus far.

168
00:10:36,708 --> 00:10:38,125
Right.

169
00:10:38,208 --> 00:10:40,166
Hey Naru. You're back.

170
00:10:40,250 --> 00:10:41,375
Yes, thank you, Mai.

171
00:10:41,458 --> 00:10:43,208
I knew that already.

172
00:10:43,291 --> 00:10:46,416
Why can't he ever act
like he does in my dreams?

173
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:47,250
What are...

174
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:48,500
Hey.

175
00:10:48,583 --> 00:10:50,000
