00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:24,916
so he plans to
perform an exorcism.

269
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:28,166
What's the difference between
an exorcism and a cleansing?

270
00:15:28,250 --> 00:15:29,916
In a cleansing you try
to persuade the spirits

271
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:31,208
to change their ways...

272
00:15:31,291 --> 00:15:32,541
but in an exorcism

273
00:15:32,625 --> 00:15:35,250
the goal is to destroy or
kill the spirit outright.

274
00:15:35,333 --> 00:15:37,625
That's horrible.

275
00:15:37,708 --> 00:15:39,958
I wish he wouldn't
exorcise her...

276
00:15:40,041 --> 00:15:42,916
At least...
not in my presence.

277
00:15:44,416 --> 00:15:46,250
Interesting...

278
00:15:46,333 --> 00:15:49,458
To Masako, spirits and
humans are one in the same.

279
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:54,416
You okay?!

280
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:57,208
Yeah. I'm fine.

281
00:15:57,291 --> 00:15:58,916
Something yanked
on my arm.

282
00:16:02,083 --> 00:16:05,250
In the beginning
was the Word.

283
00:16:05,333 --> 00:16:08,666
And the Word was with God.

284
00:16:08,750 --> 00:16:10,708
Miss Hara... How 'bout now?

285
00:16:10,791 --> 00:16:12,833
They're attempting
to escape...

286
00:16:12,916 --> 00:16:15,208
Their numbers are
beginning to drop rapidly...

287
00:16:15,291 --> 00:16:17,583
They're trying to get
out of the living room...

288
00:16:17,666 --> 00:16:19,250
and they're crying.

289
00:16:19,333 --> 00:16:20,208
Hey wait...

290
00:16:20,291 --> 00:16:21,458
Why don't you go ahead

291
00:16:21,541 --> 00:16:23,333
and cleanse the children's
spirits right now?

292
00:16:23,416 --> 00:16:24,541
Impossible...

293
00:16:24,625 --> 00:16:26,791
Not as long as the
woman's spirit is here.

294
00:16:28,375 --> 00:16:29,458
What is it?

295
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:34,750
She's coming out.

296
00:16:59,041 --> 00:17:00,250
Tomiko.

297
00:17:02,083 --> 00:17:03,541
Tomiko.

298
00:17:07,416 --> 00:17:08,625
Those eyes.

299
00:17:08,708 --> 00:17:10,458
Tomiko is not here!

300
00:17:10,541 --> 00:17:12,750
These children do
not belong to you!

301
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:14,625
Please, set them free.

302
00:17:14,708 --> 00:17:17,000
Can't you see the pain
they're suffering?

303
00:17:17,083 --> 00:17:19,791
They just want to return
to their real mothers.

304
00:17:19,875 --> 00:17:20,875
Let them go...!

305
00:17:33,333 --> 00:17:34,125
John!

306
00:17:43,166 --> 00:17:45,208
Naru...! Give me
another minute...!

307
00:17:45,291 --> 00:17:46,541
Please, don't!

308
00:17:46,625 --> 00:17:48,000
Naru wait!

309
00:17:49,916 --> 00:17:51,333
Your child is right here...

310
00:17:51,416 --> 00:17:52,541
look?

311
00:17:57,416 --> 00:17:59,083
What is that?

312
00:17:59,166 --> 00:18:01,416
Take the children you've
gathered with you...

313
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:02,791
and leave this place!

314
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:39,416
What a warm light.

315
00:18:39,500 --> 00:18:41,750
It's so beautiful.

316
00:18:41,833 --> 00:18:42,916
Look Mai... right there.

317
00:18:59,666 --> 00:19:01,458
They're all gone now...

318
00:19:01,541 --> 00:19:03,000
They've been cleansed.

319
00:19:12,041 --> 00:19:14,916
And with that,
another case was solved.

320
00:19:21,166 --> 00:19:23,916
You have no idea how
grateful I am for your help.

321
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,333
I just heard
from my brother

322
00:19:25,416 --> 00:19:27,416
and he said he'll be
returning as soon as he can.

323
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:29,125
Oh, That's great news!

324
00:19:29,208 --> 00:19:30,666
Are you sure it's safe...?

325
00:19:30,750 --> 00:19:32,083
I mean you're sure

326
00:19:32,166 --> 00:19:33,958
that you got rid of all
the ghosts in the house?

327
00:19:34,041 --> 00:19:35,625
There's no need to worry.

328
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:38,125
Last one.

329
00:19:38,208 --> 00:19:40,000
We're set to go.

330
00:19:40,083 --> 00:19:42,416
Naru. What was that little
thing you gave the ghost?

331
00:19:42,500 --> 00:19:44,000
It was a hitogata.

332
00:19:44,083 --> 00:19:46,000
What is that?

333
00:19:46,083 --> 00:19:48,708
It's the original form of
the straw effigy dolls...

334
00:19:48,791 --> 00:19:50,750
It's made by carving a
piece of Paulownia wood

335
00:19:50,833 --> 00:19:51,708
into the shape
of the person

336
00:19:51,791 --> 00:19:53,291
you want to put a spell on.

337
00:19:53,375 --> 00:19:54,458
You dummy ...

338
00:19:54,541 --> 00:19:56,500
That's how you put
a curse on someone.

339
00:19:56,583 --> 00:19:59,708
Spellcasting has both a
light and a dark side.

340
00:19:59,791 --> 00:20:01,583
A light spell
helps the person

341
00:20:01,666 --> 00:20:03,375
while a dark harms them.

342
00:20:03,458 --> 00:20:05,000
Often the casting
has a combination

343
00:20:05,083 --> 00:20:06,750
of light and dark sides.

344
00:20:06,833 --> 00:20:07,791
That's right...

345
00:20:07,875 --> 00:20:09,625
It's just like in
esoteric Buddhism,

346
00:20:09,708 --> 00:20:12,958
where either approach can be
used to confound a sworn enemy.

347
00:20:13,041 --> 00:20:16,208
The hitogata is simply a vessel
used to contain a spirit...

348
00:20:16,291 --> 00:20:19,833
For example, let's say I
patterned an effigy after Mai.

349
00:20:19,916 --> 00:20:22,250
If I were to
damage the hitogata,

350
00:20:22,333 --> 00:20:24,000
Mai would be harmed as well.

351
00:20:26,250 --> 00:20:28,750
That's how close the
effigy is to the real person.

352
00:20:28,833 --> 00:20:30,291
So that one was...

353
00:20:30,375 --> 00:20:31,708
Made for Tomiko.

354
00:20:31,791 --> 00:20:33,250
Of course...

355
00:20:33,333 --> 00:20:35,291
Since she thought she had
retrieved her daughter Tomiko,

356
00:20:35,375 --> 00:20:38,708
she was cleansed because
her wish had been fulfilled.

357
00:20:38,791 --> 00:20:40,166
I gotta to say I'm impressed

358
00:20:40,250 --> 00:20:42,416
you made a successful
hitogata that quickly.

359
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:43,791
Is that why you
had left earlier?

360
00:20:43,875 --> 00:20:46,291
The date of Tomiko's birth
and death were necessary

361
00:20:46,375 --> 00:20:48,000
for the effigy
to be effective.

362
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:51,666
The woman was Oshima Hiro.

363
00:20:51,750 --> 00:20:54,041
Tomiko was her
only child...

364
00:20:54,125 --> 00:20:55,708
The girl had
disappeared one day

365
00:20:55,791 --> 00:20:57,166
and her body surfaced
from the pond

366
00:20:57,250 --> 00:20:59,333
about six months later.

367
00:20:59,416 --> 00:21:00,875
A couple of
years after that,

368
00:21:00,958 --> 00:21:02,916
Oshima's house
was demolished...

369
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:05,333
and the house before us
now was built in its place.

370
00:21:05,416 --> 00:21:06,916
Tomiko...

371
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:09,625
Do we know if,
she was kidnapped?

372
00:21:09,708 --> 00:21:11,958
Is that why the mother
threw herself down the well?

373
00:21:14,166 --> 00:21:17,083
There was no mention
of a kidnapping...

374
00:21:17,166 --> 00:21:19,625
The important thing is that
this house is free of spirits.

375
00:21:20,791 --> 00:21:22,250
I wonder...

376
00:21:22,333 --> 00:21:23,833
Were you planning
on a cleansing

377
00:21:23,916 --> 00:21:25,333
from the very beginning, Naru?

378
00:21:31,041 --> 00:21:33,291
I never would have pegged
him as an Onmyouji!

379
00:21:33,375 --> 00:21:34,791
Onmyouji...?

380
00:21:34,875 --> 00:21:36,958
Do you mean like
that Abe guy?

381
00:21:37,041 --> 00:21:39,041
Fashioning a hitogata
after Tomiko

382
00:21:39,125 --> 00:21:41,750
and cleansing the mother
is pretty complicated...

383
00:21:41,833 --> 00:21:43,791
Only a pro can
pull that off.

384
00:21:43,875 --> 00:21:45,208
It's amazing isn't it...?

385
00:21:45,291 --> 00:21:46,750
With how young Naru is.

386
00:21:46,833 --> 00:21:48,000
Amazing?

387
00:21:48,083 --> 00:21:49,916
Well it's definitely cool.

388
00:21:51,750 --> 00:21:54,416
-Hey Mai!
-Hey...! What's up Ayami?

389
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:56,166
So Do you think...

390
00:21:56,250 --> 00:21:57,833
we'll see each
other again?

391
00:22:01,541 --> 00:22:02,416
I'll tell you what.

392
00:22:02,500 --> 00:22:05,000
If you ever need me,
just call.

393
00:22:05,083 --> 00:22:08,083
-You promise?
-Promise.

394
00:22:08,166 --> 00:22:09,375
At the end of the day,

395
00:22:09,458 --> 00:22:11,375
I'm just happy that
Ayami is safe.

396
00:22:17,375 --> 00:22:23,083
[Music]

397
00:23:49,625 --> 00:23:51,041
Next time on Ghost Hunt,

398
00:23:51,125 --> 00:23:53,291
the After School Hexer,
part one!

399
